{"title": "wonderful History of Peter Schlemihl, the Man who lost his Shadow", "description": "Peter Schlemihl is an ordinary man until one day he bargains with the devil: He trades his shadow for a bottomless purse. While this sounds like a good idea at first, it turns out that having no shadow is considered to be so strange by society, that even unlimited wealth cannot repair such a fault.<br></br> The story of Peter Schlemihl is exceedingly well-known even today, but the original text is not so widely-read as it once was. This very accessible translation by F.H. Hedge may be a good introduction to modern listeners.  - Summary by Carolin", "duration": 9550, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "4909", "name": " Adelbert von Chamisso"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/peter_schlemihl_1711_librivox/peterschlemihl_1711.jpg", "copyright_year": "1899", "genres": ["Fantastic Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Crln Yldz Ksr"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Crln Yldz Ksr"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Devorah Allen"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [11051], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/peter_schlemihl_1711_librivox/peterschlemihl_00_chamisso_64kb.mp3", "duration": 566}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I", "readers": [11701], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/peter_schlemihl_1711_librivox/peterschlemihl_01_chamisso_64kb.mp3", "duration": 941}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II", "readers": [11051], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/peter_schlemihl_1711_librivox/peterschlemihl_02_chamisso_64kb.mp3", "duration": 933}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter III", "readers": [11701], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/peter_schlemihl_1711_librivox/peterschlemihl_03_chamisso_64kb.mp3", "duration": 591}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter IV", "readers": [11701], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/pete